'''Mount Ollivier''' is a {{convert|1933|m|ft|abbr=on}} mountain in the [[Canterbury Region]] of [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{LINZ|9306||2009-04-25}}</ref> It is a peak in the [[Sealy Range]], about {{convert|2.5|km|mi|abbr=on}} west of [[Mount Cook Village]]. The peak is named after mountaineer [[Arthur Ollivier]], who died in 1897.<ref name="NZHerald10487471">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10487471|title=Renaming peak for Sir Ed meets resistance |last=Booker|first=Jarrod|date=18 January 2008|publisher=New Zealand Herald|accessdate=2009-04-25}}</ref>

Mount Ollivier was [[Edmund Hillary|Sir Edmund Hillary]]'s first major climb, in 1939. After his death in 2008, there was a proposal to rename the peak Mount Hillary as a memorial.<ref name="NZHerald10487471"/>

